
Version 2

Removed scripting
Changed interface
Added mesh importing and new primitives

Implemented JPEG-like compression for textures
Improved encoding and decoding for integers
Added progress bar for heavy tasks and prevented page freezing

Reduced texture encoding time by 75% !!! :O

Objects can now have different tints and UV scales independent from their materials
Changed how scenes are loaded into Three.js to be less confusing and overall just better
Removed remnants of old JSON based file format

Texture compression uses YCBCR instead of RGB; Compressed textures are now 66% the size compared to previous encoding
Individal channels can be omitted from textures, making storage of greyscale or non-transparent images more efficient
Loader and saver has been fixed
Models are now automatically scaled when imported

Fleshed out scripting language